  "prompt": "What are the steps for registering a company in India?",
  "response": "Here are the steps for registering a company in India:\n\n1. Initial Preparation\n- Choose a company name\n- Determine company type (Private Limited, Public Limited, etc.)\n- Decide company structure and shareholders\n\n2. Digital Signature Certificate (DSC)\n- Apply for digital signatures for directors\n- Obtain DSC from authorized agencies\n\n3. Director Identification Number (DIN)\n- Apply for DIN through online portal\n- Submit required documents\n- Get unique identification number for directors\n\n4. Name Reservation\n- Check name availability on Ministry of Corporate Affairs (MCA) website\n- Apply for name reservation\n- Obtain name approval\n\n5. Incorporation Documents\n- Prepare Memorandum of Association (MOA)\n- Prepare Articles of Association (AOA)\n- Collect mandatory documents from directors/shareholders\n\n6. Filing Incorporation Application\n- File electronic form (SPICe) on MCA portal\n- Submit required documents\n- Pay registration fees\n\n7. Certificate of Incorporation\n- Receive Certificate of Incorporation from Registrar of Companies\n- Get Company Permanent Account Number (PAN)\n- Obtain Tax Deduction and Collection Account Number (TAN)\n\n8. Post-registration Compliance\n- Open corporate bank account\n- Apply for GST registration\n- Fulfill other statutory requirements",
